name: FieldLocate
description: Add an FieldLocate FSA Instance to connect your existing FieldLocate account to the FSA Hub, allowing you to manage your invoices, products, customers, etc. across multiple FSA Elements. You will need your FieldLocate API key to add an instance.

configuration.name: The FieldLocate Subdomain
configuration.description:
Subdomain of your company, ex: https://abc.fieldlocate.com, the
  subdomain will be abc

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Event poller token map
configuration.description: Used to store the api changeset tokens

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used for how often to poll the application (in minutes)

configuration.name: List Objects to Poll
configuration.description: Comma separated list of objects to poll.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for jobs last modified on or after Jan 15, 2014, the search expression will be where: [lastModifiedDate=2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z]. When this parameter is omitted, all accounts are returned in a paginated fashion.
